# Website Link / Href Navigation

Applies to any website UI that navigates between routes. Authorities: `@my-ssr/web-core` `src/components/Link.tsx`, `src/types/router.ts` (`Href`, `To`, `BrowserNavigator`); `website/src/app/ui/base/hooks/useNav.tsx`; `website/src/resources/configs/routes.ts` (`MPagesRoutes`).

## Cross-page navigation — use `Link`, not `<a>`

Internal cross-page navigation MUST use the `Link` component from `@my-ssr/web-core`. Do NOT render a raw `<a>` (or `As={"a"}`) for an internal route. `Link` renders a real `<a href>` (so SEO, middle-click, and open-in-new-tab work) but intercepts the click and calls `getRouter().getNav().push(to)` — client-side transition with no full reload.

`Link` accepts `to` or `href` (alias: `to = to || href`) typed as `string | "CURRENT" | To<Ident>`, plus `external`, `replace`, `redirect`, `query`, `state`, `status`.

## Typed `Href` — object, not string

`Href<Ident> = { identify: Ident, replace?, sub? } & ParamsQuery<Ident>` (or `{ identify: "CURRENT", params?, query?, replace? }`). `To<Ident> = Href<Ident> & { state? }`.

- Pass a **typed object** `{ identify: "Login" }` (a `Href<keyof MPagesRoutes>` / `To<...>`), NOT a raw string path like `"/login"`. The object form is type-checked against `MPagesRoutes`; a typo in `identify` fails `yarn type-check`.
- `MPagesRoutes` is the website-local route interface in `routes.ts`. Current members: `Login`, `Home`, `UiMockup` (`Error` comes from web-core's `PagesRoutes`). 

## Adding a target page = TWO edits

To wire a new navigable page (e.g. `Register`, `About`, `Terms`):

1. Add it to the `routes` map in `routes.ts` (`path`, `layout`, `preLoadedPage`/`pageLoader`).
2. Declare it in the `MPagesRoutes` interface in `routes.ts` (so `Href<keyof MPagesRoutes>` accepts `{ identify: "Register" }`).

Until both edits exist, the page is unimplemented → callers MUST pass `href: undefined` (the `Link` renders without a destination). Do NOT pass a fake string path or a guessed `identify` — it would either type-error or 404.

## Combining `Link` with Utils styling

`Utils` (`Box`/`Text`/`Row`/`Col`) forward the `extra` prop to the underlying element. To style a `Link` with Utils, render `<Text As={Link} ... extra={{ href, ... }}>` (or `<Box As={Link}>`):

- `Link`-specific props (`href`/`to`/`external`/`replace`/`redirect`/`query`/`state`) go through `extra` (they are not Utils props).
- Utils style props (`clr`, `variant`, `baseCssStyle`, `cssStyle`, …) apply normally; `...ElementStyles.buttonReset` in `baseCssStyle` is valid for an anchor rendered as a button-like control.
- `textDecoration: "none"` belongs in `cssStyle` (no shorthand) when resetting link underline.

Canonical example — `LandingFooterLink` (`website/src/app/ui/components/LandingFooter.tsx`): `<Text As={Link} extra={{ href: link.href /* Href<keyof MPagesRoutes> | undefined */, title, "aria-label" }}>`.

## Programmatic navigation — `useNav().push`

For navigation triggered from a button `onClick` (not a link), use `useNav()` from `website/src/app/ui/base/hooks/useNav` (returns `BrowserNavigator`): `push({ identify: "Login" })` for a route, `push("CURRENT")` to refresh. `useNav` is CSR-only (returns `{}` on the server), so it is safe to call inside event handlers but MUST NOT be invoked during render/SSR.

## External links

Use `Link` with `external` (or a plain `<a>`) ONLY for external URLs (different origin). `external` makes `Link` render `<a href={to} target="_blank">` with NO click interception — a full reload in a new tab. Never use `external` for an internal route (it would bypass client-side routing).

## In-page section navigation is scroll-based, NOT route-based

Navigation between sections of the SAME page (landing sections) uses `scrollIntoView` (`scrollToLandingSection` / `scrollToLandingTop` in `landing-layout/drawer.ts`), not `Link`/`push`. Do not invent a route per section. The active section is derived client-side from `useActiveLandingSection` (IntersectionObserver) — see W55.

## Forbidden

- Raw `<a>` / `As={"a"}` with a string `href` for an internal route (bypasses client-side nav → full reload).
- Passing a raw string path to `Link`/`push` when a typed `Href` object is expected.
- Passing a fake `identify` for an unimplemented page instead of `undefined`.
- Using `external` for an internal route.
- Using `Link`/`push` for same-page section jumps (use scroll).

